trans-unit.source: JSDoc 3 is an API documentation generator for JavaScript, similar to Javadoc or phpDocumentor. You add documentation comments directly to your source code, right alongside the code itself. The JSDoc tool will scan your source code and generate an HTML documentation website for you.

trans-unit.source: JSDoc 3 makes it easy to document classes that follow the ECMAScript 2015 specification. trans-unit.source: The @async tag indicates that a function is asynchronous, meaning that it was declared using the syntax async function foo() {}. Do not use this tag for other types of asynchronous functions, such as functions that provide a callback. This tag is available in JSDoc 3.5.0 and later.
trans-unit.target: 所述 @async 标签指示的功能是异步的，这意味着它是使用的语法声明 async function foo() {} 。请勿将此标签用于其他类型的异步函数，例如提供回调的函数。JSDoc 3.5.0及更高版本中提供了此标记。

trans-unit.source: The @augments or@extends tag indicates that a symbol inherits from, and potentially adds to, a parent symbol. You can use this tag to document both class-based and prototype-based inheritance.
trans-unit.target: 所述 @augments 或 @extends 标签指示从一个符号继承，并潜在地增加了，一个父符号。您可以使用此标记来记录基于类和基于原型的继承。

trans-unit.source: The @external tag identifies a class, namespace, or module that is defined outside of the current package. By using this tag, you can document your package's extensions to the external symbol, or you can provide information about the external symbol to your package's users. You can also refer to the external symbol's namepath in any other JSDoc tag.
trans-unit.target: 所述 @external 标记用于标识类，命名空间，或者是定义的当前封装外部模块。通过使用此标记，您可以记录软件包对外部符号的扩展名，或者可以将有关外部符号的信息提供给软件包的用户。您还可以在任何其他JSDoc标记中引用外部符号的名称路径。

trans-unit.source: The @generator tag indicates that a function is a generator function, meaning that it was declared using the syntax function* foo() {}. This tag is available in JSDoc 3.5.0 and later.
trans-unit.target: 该 @generator 标签指示的功能是生成器功能，这意味着它被宣布使用语法 function* foo() {} 。JSDoc 3.5.0及更高版本中提供了此标记。

trans-unit.source: The @hideconstructor tag tells JSDoc that the generated documentation should not display the constructor for a class. This tag is available in JSDoc 3.5.0 and later.
trans-unit.target: 该 @hideconstructor 标签告诉JSDoc的是，生成的文档不应该显示为一个类的构造函数。JSDoc 3.5.0及更高版本中提供了此标记。

trans-unit.source: The @ignore tag indicates that a symbol in your code should never appear in the documentation. This tag takes precedence over all others.
trans-unit.target: 该 @ignore 标签表明，在你的代码符号不应该出现在文档。此标记优先于所有其他标记。

trans-unit.source: The @implements tag indicates that a symbol implements an interface.
trans-unit.target: 该 @implements 标签指示符号实现一个接口。

trans-unit.source: The @inheritdoc tag indicates that a symbol should inherit its documentation from its parent class. Any other tags that you include in the JSDoc comment will be ignored.
trans-unit.target: 该 @inheritdoc 标签指示符号应继承其父类的文档。您包含在JSDoc注释中的任何其他标签将被忽略。

trans-unit.source: The @interface tag marks a symbol as an interface that other symbols can implement. For example, your code might define a parent class whose methods and properties are stubbed out. You can add the @interface tag to the parent class to indicate that child classes must implement the parent class' methods and properties.
trans-unit.target: 该 @interface 标签标记的符号为其他符号可以实现一个接口。例如，您的代码可能会定义一个父类，其方法和属性均已存根。您可以在父类中添加 @interface 标记，以指示子类必须实现父类的方法和属性。

trans-unit.source: The @lends tag allows you to document all the members of an object literal as if they were members of a symbol with the given name. You might want to do this if you are passing an object literal into a function that creates a named class from its members.
trans-unit.target: 该 @lends 标签可以让你对象文本的所有成员，如果他们与给定的名称符号的成员记录。如果要将对象文字传递到从其成员创建命名类的函数中，则可能需要执行此操作。

trans-unit.source: The @license tag identifies the software license that applies to any portion of your code.
trans-unit.target: 该 @license 标签标识适用于你的代码的任何部分的软件许可证。

trans-unit.source: The @listens tag indicates that a symbol listens for the specified event. Use the @event tag to document the event's content.
trans-unit.target: 该 @listens 标记表明指定事件的象征监听。使用 @event tag 记录事件的内容。

trans-unit.source: The @override tag indicates that a symbol overrides a symbol with the same name in a parent class.
trans-unit.target: 该 @override 标签指示符号会覆盖在父类中相同名称的符号。

trans-unit.source: The @package tag is equivalent to @access package.
trans-unit.target: 该 @package 标签相当于 @access package 。

trans-unit.source: The @package tag marks a symbol as package-private. Typically, this tag indicates that a symbol is available only to code in the same directory as the source file for this symbol. This tag is available in JSDoc 3.5.0 and later.
trans-unit.target: 该 @package 标签标记的符号作为包私有。通常，此标记指示符号仅可用于与该符号的源文件位于同一目录中的代码。JSDoc 3.5.0及更高版本中提供了此标记。

trans-unit.source: The @param tag provides the name, type, and description of a function parameter.
trans-unit.target: 在 @param 标签提供的名称，类型和函数参数的描述。

trans-unit.source: The @param tag requires you to specify the name of the parameter you are documenting. You can also include the parameter's type, enclosed in curly brackets, and a description of the parameter.
trans-unit.target: 该 @param 标签要求您指定要记录的参数的名称。您还可以包括参数的类型（用大括号括起来）和参数说明。

trans-unit.source: The @private tag is equivalent to @access private.
trans-unit.target: 该 @private 标签相当于 @access private 。

trans-unit.source: The @private tag is not inherited by child members. For example, if the @private tag is added to a namespace, members of the namespace can still appear in the generated output; because the namespace is private, the members' namepath will not include the namespace.
trans-unit.target: 该 @private 标签不被子成员继承。例如，如果将 @private 标记添加到名称空间，则该名称空间的成员仍可以出现在生成的输出中。因为名称空间是私有的，所以成员的名称路径将不包含名称空间。

trans-unit.source: The @private tag marks a symbol as private, or not meant for general use. Private members are not shown in the generated output unless JSDoc is run with the -p/--private command-line option. In JSDoc 3.3.0 and later, you can also use the -a/--access command-line option to change this behavior.
trans-unit.target: 该 @private 标签标记的符号为私有，或不用于一般用途。除非使用 -p/--private -private 命令行选项运行JSDoc，否则私有成员不会显示在生成的输出中。在JSDoc 3.3.0和更高版本中，您还可以使用 -a/--access -access 命令行选项来更改此行为。

trans-unit.source: The @protected tag is equivalent to @access protected.
trans-unit.target: 该 @protected 标签相当于 @access protected 。

trans-unit.source: The @protected tag marks a symbol as protected. Typically, this tag indicates that a symbol is only available, or should only be used, within the current module.
trans-unit.target: 该 @protected 标签标记的符号作为保护。通常，此标签指示符号仅在当前模块中可用或应使用。

trans-unit.source: The @public tag indicates that a symbol should be documented as if it were public.
trans-unit.target: 该 @public 标签表明，就好像它是一个公共符号应记录在案。

trans-unit.source: The @returns tag documents the value that a function returns.
trans-unit.target: 该 @returns 标签文档的价值，一个函数返回。

trans-unit.source: The @tutorial tag inserts a link to a tutorial file that is provided as part of the documentation. See the tutorials overview for instructions on creating tutorials.
trans-unit.target: 所述 @tutorial 标签插入一个链接到作为文件的一部分提供一个教程文件。有关创建教程的说明，请参见教程概述。

trans-unit.source: The @yields tag documents the value that is yielded by a generator function. This tag is available in JSDoc 3.5.0 and later.
trans-unit.target: 该 @yields 标签文档是由生成器函数的值。JSDoc 3.5.0及更高版本中提供了此标记。

trans-unit.source: The README.md file to include in the generated documentation. Defaults to the first README.md file found in the source paths.
trans-unit.target: 该 README.md 文件，包括生成的文档。默认为在源路径中找到的第一个 README.md 文件。

trans-unit.source: The beforeParse event is fired before parsing has begun. Plugins can use this method to modify the source code that will be parsed. For instance, your plugin could add a JSDoc comment, or it could remove preprocessing tags that are not valid JavaScript.
trans-unit.target: 该 beforeParse 解析开始之前触发事件。插件可以使用此方法来修改将要解析的源代码。例如，您的插件可以添加JSDoc注释，或者可以删除不是有效JavaScript的预处理标签。

trans-unit.source: The defineTag method returns a Tag object, which has a synonym method that can be used to declare a synonym for the tag.
trans-unit.target: 该 defineTag 方法返回一个 Tag 对象，它具有一个 synonym 可用于声明为标记的同义词方法。

trans-unit.source: The fileBegin event is fired when the parser is about to parse a file. Your plugin can use this event to trigger per-file initialization if necessary.
trans-unit.target: 该 fileBegin 当解析器即将解析文件事件。如果需要，您的插件可以使用此事件触发每个文件的初始化。

trans-unit.source: The fileComplete event is fired when the parser has finished parsing a file. Your plugin could use this event to trigger per-file cleanup.
trans-unit.target: 该 fileComplete 当解析器完成解析文件事件。您的插件可以使用此事件触发每个文件的清理。

trans-unit.source: The jsdocCommentFound event is fired whenever a JSDoc comment is found. The comment may or may not be associated with any code. You might use this event to modify the contents of a comment before it is processed.
trans-unit.target: 该 jsdocCommentFound 每当JSDoc评论发现事件。注释可能与或未与任何代码关联。您可以使用此事件在处理注释之前修改其内容。

trans-unit.source: The newDoclet event is the highest-level event. It is fired when a new doclet has been created. This means that a JSDoc comment or a symbol has been processed, and the actual doclet that will be passed to the template has been created.
trans-unit.target: 该 newDoclet 事件是最高级别的会议。创建新的doclet后将触发该事件。这意味着已经处理了JSDoc注释或符号，并且已经创建了将传递到模板的实际doclet。

trans-unit.source: The package.json file must use npm's package format.
trans-unit.target: 该 package.json 文件必须使用故宫的包格式。

trans-unit.source: The package.json file that contains the project name, version, and other details. Defaults to the first package.json file found in the source paths.
trans-unit.target: 包含项目名称，版本和其他详细信息的 package.json 文件。默认为在源路径中找到的第一个 package.json 文件。

trans-unit.source: The parseBegin event is fired before JSDoc starts loading and parsing the source files. Your plugin can control which files JSDoc will parse by modifying the event's contents.
trans-unit.target: 该 parseBegin 事件之前JSDoc开始加载和解析源文件被解雇。您的插件可以通过修改事件的内容来控制JSDoc将解析哪些文件。

trans-unit.source: The parseComplete event is fired after JSDoc has parsed all of the specified source files.
trans-unit.target: 该 parseComplete JSDoc解析了所有指定的源文件后，事件被触发。

trans-unit.source: The processingComplete event is fired after JSDoc updates the parse results to reflect inherited and borrowed symbols.
trans-unit.target: 该 processingComplete 事件被触发JSDoc更新解析结果，以反映继承和借来的符号之后。

trans-unit.source: The recurseDepth option controls how many levels deep JSDoc will recursively search for source files and tutorials. This option is available in JSDoc 3.5.0 and later. This option is used only if you also specify the -r command-line flag, which tells JSDoc to recursively search for input files.
trans-unit.target: 该 recurseDepth 选项控制多少级深JSDoc将递归搜索源文件和教程。JSDoc 3.5.0及更高版本中提供了此选项。仅当您还指定了 -r 命令行标志时，才使用此选项，该标志告诉JSDoc递归搜索输入文件。

trans-unit.source: The source set of options, in combination with paths given to JSDoc on the command line, determines the set of input files that JSDoc uses to generate documentation.
trans-unit.target: 选项的 source 集，以及在命令行上给JSDoc给出的路径，决定了JSDoc用于生成文档的输入文件集。

trans-unit.source: The symbolFound event is fired when the parser comes across a symbol in the code that may need to be documented. For example, the parser fires a symbolFound event for each variable, function, and object literal in a source file.
trans-unit.target: 该 symbolFound 当解析器遇到一个符号可能需要被记录的代码事件。例如，解析器为源文件中的每个变量，函数和对象文字触发一个 symbolFound 事件。

trans-unit.source: The tags.allowUnknownTags property affects how JSDoc handles unrecognized tags. If you set this option to false, and JSDoc finds a tag that it does not recognize (for example, @foo), JSDoc logs a warning. By default, this option is set to true. In JSDoc 3.4.1 and later, you can also set this property to an array of tag names that JSDoc should allow (for example, ["foo","bar"]).
trans-unit.target: 该 tags.allowUnknownTags 属性影响JSDoc如何处理无法识别的标签。如果将此选项设置为 false ，并且JSDoc找到它无法识别的标签（例如 @foo ），则JSDoc会记录一条警告。默认情况下，此选项设置为 true 。在JSDoc 3.4.1和更高版本中，您也可以将此属性设置为JSDoc应该允许的标记名数组（例如 ["foo","bar"] ）。

trans-unit.target: 该 tags.dictionaries 其标签JSDoc认识，以及如何JSDoc解释标签，它识别属性控制。在JSDoc 3.3.0和更高版本中，有两个内置的标签字典：

trans-unit.source: The {@link} inline tag creates a link to the namepath or URL that you specify. When you use the {@link} tag, you can also provide link text, using one of several different formats. If you don't provide any link text, JSDoc uses the namepath or URL as the link text.
trans-unit.target: 该 {@link} 内嵌标签创建的链接名路径名或URL您指定。使用 {@link} 标记时，还可以使用几种不同格式之一提供链接文本。如果您不提供任何链接文本，则JSDoc使用名称路径或URL作为链接文本。

trans-unit.source: The {@tutorial} inline tag creates a link to the tutorial identifier that you specify. When you use the {@tutorial} tag, you can also provide link text, using one of several different formats. If you don't provide any link text, JSDoc uses the tutorial's title as the link text.
trans-unit.target: 该 {@tutorial} 内嵌标签创建您所指定教程标识的链接。使用 {@tutorial} 标记时，还可以使用几种不同格式之一提供链接文本。如果您不提供任何链接文本，那么JSDoc将使用本教程的标题作为链接文本。

trans-unit.source: The @abstract tag identifies members that must be implemented (or overridden) by objects that inherit the member.
trans-unit.target: @abstract标签标识了必须由继承该成员的对象实现(或重写)的成员。

trans-unit.source: The @alias tag causes JSDoc to treat all references to a member as if the member had a different name. This tag is especially useful if you define a class within an inner function; in this case, you can use the @alias tag to tell JSDoc how the class is exposed in your app.
trans-unit.target: @alias 标签会使 JSDoc 将所有对成员的引用视为该成员有不同的名称。如果您在一个内部函数中定义了一个类,这个标签就特别有用;在这种情况下,您可以使用 @alias 标签来告诉 JSDoc 如何在您的应用程序中暴露该类。

trans-unit.source: The @author tag identifies the author of an item. In JSDoc 3.2 and later, if the author's name is followed by an email address enclosed in angle brackets, the default template will convert the email address to a mailto: link.
trans-unit.target: @author标记标识项目的作者。在JSDoc 3.2和更高版本中，如果作者的名字后跟带有尖括号的电子邮件地址，则默认模板会将电子邮件地址转换为 mailto: 链接。

trans-unit.source: The @borrows tag allows you to add documentation for another symbol to your documentation.
trans-unit.target: 通过@borrows标签,您可以将另一个符号的文档添加到您的文档中。

trans-unit.source: The @callback tag provides information about a callback function that can be passed to other functions, including the callback's parameters and return value. You can include any of the tags that you can provide for a @method.
trans-unit.target: @callback标签提供了一个回调函数的信息,这些信息可以传递给其他函数,包括回调的参数和返回值。你可以包含任何你可以为@method提供的标签。

trans-unit.source: The @class tag marks a function as being a constructor, meant to be called with the new keyword to return an instance.
trans-unit.target: @class标签标志着一个函数是一个构造函数,意在用new关键字调用以返回一个实例。

trans-unit.source: The @classdesc tag is used to provide a description for a class, separate from the constructor function's description. Use the @classdesc tag in combination with the @class (or @constructor) tag.
trans-unit.target: @classdesc标记用于提供类的描述，与构造函数的描述分开。将@classdesc标记与@class（或@constructor）标记结合使用。

trans-unit.source: The @constant tag is used to mark the documentation as belonging to a symbol that is a constant.

trans-unit.source: The @copyright tag is used to document copyright information in a file overview comment. Use this tag in combination with the @file tag.

trans-unit.source: The @default tag allows you to document the assigned value of a symbol. You can supply this tag with a value yourself or you can allow JSDoc to automatically document the value from the source code -- only possible when the documented symbol is being assigned a single, simple value that is either: a string, a number, a boolean or null.

trans-unit.source: The @deprecated tag marks a symbol in your code as being deprecated.
trans-unit.target: @deprecated标签标志着你的代码中的一个符号被废弃了。

trans-unit.source: The @description tag allows you to provide a general description of the symbol you are documenting. The description may include HTML markup. It may also include Markdown formatting if the Markdown plugin is enabled.
trans-unit.target: @description标记使您可以提供正在记录的符号的一般说明。该描述可以包括HTML标记。如果启用了Markdown插件，则还可能包括Markdown格式。

trans-unit.source: The @enum tag documents a collection of static properties whose values are all of the same type.
trans-unit.target: @enum标签记录了一个静态属性的集合,这些属性的值都是相同的类型。

trans-unit.source: The @event tag allows you to document an event that can be fired. A typical event is represented by an object with a defined set of properties.
trans-unit.target: @event标签允许你记录一个可以被触发的事件。一个典型的事件由一个具有定义属性集的对象来表示。

trans-unit.source: The @file tag provides a description for a file. Use the tag in a JSDoc comment at the beginning of the file.
trans-unit.target: @file标签提供了一个文件的描述。在文件开头的JSDoc注释中使用该标签。

trans-unit.source: The @fires tag indicates that a method can fire a specified type of event when it is called. Use the @event tag to document the event's content.
trans-unit.target: @fires标记表示方法可以在调用时触发指定类型的事件。使用@event标签记录事件的内容。

trans-unit.source: The @global tag specifies that a symbol should appear in the documentation as a global symbol. JSDoc ignores the symbol's actual scope within the source file. This tag is especially useful for symbols that are defined locally, then assigned to a global symbol.
trans-unit.target: @global标记指定符号应在文档中作为全局符号出现。JSDoc会忽略源文件中符号的实际范围。此标记对于在本地定义然后分配给全局符号的符号特别有用。

trans-unit.source: The @kind tag is used to document what kind of symbol is being documented (for example, a class or a module). The kind of symbol differs from a symbol's type (for example, string or boolean).
trans-unit.target: @kind标记用于记录正在记录的符号类型（例如，类或模块）。的种类从一个符号的符号不同的类型（例如，字符串或布尔值）。

trans-unit.source: The @member tag identifies any member that does not have a more specialized kind, such as "class", "function", or "constant". A member can optionally have a type as well as a name.
trans-unit.target: @member 标签标识任何没有更专门的种类,如 "类"、"函数 "或 "常量 "的成员。一个成员可以有一个类型和名称。

trans-unit.source: The @memberof tag identifies a member symbol that belongs to a parent symbol.
trans-unit.target: @memberof标签标识一个属于父符号的成员符号。

trans-unit.source: The @mixes tag indicates that the current object mixes in all the members from OtherObjectPath, which is a @mixin.
trans-unit.target: 所述@mixes标签指示在从所有成员当前对象混合 OtherObjectPath ，这是一个@mixin。

trans-unit.source: The @module tag marks the current file as being its own module. All symbols in the file are assumed to be members of the module unless documented otherwise.
trans-unit.target: @module标签标志着当前文件是它自己的模块。除非另有说明,否则文件中的所有符号都被认为是该模块的成员。

trans-unit.source: The @name tag forces JSDoc to associate the remainder of the JSDoc comment with the given name, ignoring all surrounding code. This tag is best used in "virtual comments" for symbols that are not readily visible in the code, such as methods that are generated at runtime.
trans-unit.target: @name 标签强制 JSDoc 将 JSDoc 注释的其余部分与给定的名称相关联,而忽略所有周围的代码。这个标签最好用于代码中不可见的符号的 "虚拟注释 "中,例如在运行时生成的方法。

trans-unit.source: The @namespace tag indicates that an object creates a namespace for its members. You can also write a virtual JSDoc comment that defines a namespace used by your code.
trans-unit.target: @namespace标签表示一个对象为其成员创建了一个命名空间。你也可以写一个虚拟的JSDoc注释来定义你的代码使用的命名空间。

trans-unit.source: The @property tag is a way to easily document a list of static properties of a class, namespace or other object.
trans-unit.target: @property标签是一种轻松记录一个类、命名空间或其他对象的静态属性列表的方式。

trans-unit.source: The @readonly tag indicates that a symbol is intended to be read-only. Note this is for the purpose of documentation only - JSDoc won't check whether you've actually treated the symbol as read-only in your code.
trans-unit.target: @readonly标记表示符号应为只读。请注意，这仅出于文档目的-JSDoc不会检查您是否在代码中实际将符号视为只读。

trans-unit.source: The @requires tag allows you to document that a module is needed to use this code. A JSDoc comment can have multiple @require tags. The module name can be specified as "moduleName" or "module:moduleName"; both forms will be interpreted as modules.
trans-unit.target: @requires标签允许你记录使用这段代码需要一个模块。一个JSDoc注释可以有多个@require标签。模块名称可以指定为 "moduleName "或 "module:moduleName";这两种形式都会被解释为模块。

trans-unit.source: The @see tag allows you to refer to another symbol or resource that may be related to the one being documented. You can provide either a symbol's namepath or free-form text. If you provide a namepath, JSDoc's default template automatically converts the namepath to a link.
trans-unit.target: 通过@see标签,您可以引用可能与被记录的符号或资源相关的另一个符号或资源。您可以提供一个符号的namepath或自由格式的文本。如果您提供了一个namepath,JSDoc的默认模板会自动将namepath转换为一个链接。

trans-unit.source: The @since tag indicates that a class, method, or other symbol was added in a specific version.
trans-unit.target: @since标签表示在特定版本中添加了一个类、方法或其他符号。

trans-unit.source: The @static tag indicates that a symbol is contained within a parent and can be accessed without instantiating the parent.
trans-unit.target: @static标签表示一个符号被包含在父代中,并且可以在不实例化父代的情况下被访问。

trans-unit.source: The @summary tag is a shorter version of the full description. It can be added to any doclet.
trans-unit.target: @summary标签是完整描述的缩写。它可以被添加到任何doclet中。

trans-unit.source: The @this tag indicates what the this keyword refers to when used within another symbol.
trans-unit.target: @this标记指示在另一个符号中使用 this 关键字时所指的含义。

trans-unit.source: The @throws tag allows you to document an error that a function might throw. You can include the @throws tag more than once in a single JSDoc comment.
trans-unit.target: @throws标签允许你记录一个函数可能会抛出的错误,你可以在一个JSDoc注释中包含多个@throws标签。你可以在一个JSDoc注释中包含多个@throws标签。

trans-unit.source: The @todo tag allows you to document tasks to be completed for some part of your code. You can use the @todo tag more than once in a single JSDoc comment.
trans-unit.target: @todo标签允许您记录您的代码中某些部分需要完成的任务。你可以在一个JSDoc注释中使用@todo标签多于一次。

trans-unit.source: The @type tag allows you to provide a type expression identifying the type of value that a symbol may contain, or the type of value returned by a function. You can also include type expressions with many other JSDoc tags, such as the @param tag.
trans-unit.target: @type标记使您可以提供一个类型表达式，以标识符号可能包含的值的类型或函数返回的值的类型。您还可以在许多其他JSDoc标签中包含类型表达式，例如@param标签。

trans-unit.source: The @typedef tag is useful for documenting custom types, particularly if you wish to refer to them repeatedly. These types can then be used within other tags expecting a type, such as @type or @param.
trans-unit.target: @typedef标记对于记录自定义类型很有用，特别是如果您希望重复引用它们的话。然后，可以在其他需要类型的标记中使用这些类型，例如@type或@param。
